cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is about human pose estimation, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the design of a lightweight network, which falls under the category of machine learning. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of attention mechanisms, which is a popular topic in neural networks, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed method on a benchmark dataset, which is a common practice in multimedia research, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible sub-category as well.
